<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-21T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-21T08:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/898: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-21T15:00:00+02:00">April 21, 1936—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 21—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>12. Department’s 17, April 20, 5 p.m. Reports are officially denied.
                            While such a move might be welcomed by military its execution at the
                            present time seems highly unlikely in view of the nature of Turkish
                            diplomatic <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> concerning Straits and
                            reception generally accorded to it.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>